review_blob: Nothing stands out in its appearance, semi-cloudy, medium yellow body with medium white head that fades pretty quick. Aroma is fruity, pineapple with hints of pine. Taste is mild, slightly sweet, but not overpowering. Mild and somewhat refreshing.
Black body with a purplish tan head. Aroma is burned toffee and caramel. Taste is bitter, although not the worst Ive had. Not as good as I expected, More IPA than stout.
Translucent amber body with with a thick white head. Aroma is sweet with a slightly moldy accent. Taste is hops & carmel, yet balanced right, not overly sweet, with a clean finish. Not bad.

Caught my eye at my local HyVee, love Euro lagers and a name like Krftig sounds Euro enough. Aroma is corn, dough and slight copper. Pours a pale gold with hardly any carbonation and virtually no head. Taste is grains, corn with a watery finish. Not the worst, but I wanted to like it more.
Classic yellow body with a a nice white head and good lacing. Aroma is grains, grass and a little skunky. Taste is smooth classic Euro-lager. Clean finish, enjoyable.
Nice orange body with a medium white head. Hoppy aroma with hints of spice. Taste is hops, grass and dough. Slightly mild for a pale ale with a fairly clean finish.
Better than expected. An exceptionally pale yellow body with a thin white head. Citrus, spice aroma and the taste is mild lemon and hops. Drinks pretty easy and finishes clean, recommended.
Light yellow body with thin white head a virtually no carbonation. Aroma is faint, almost doughy. Taste is sweet, but overly. Some hops, and watery. Not bad, not that impressive either.
Medium orange body with a thin white head and nice lacing. Fruity aroma with hints of spice. Taste is hoppy, bread and again spice. Fairly mild with a relatively clean finish.
Pours a deep brown with a nice tan head with nice lacing. Aroma is roasted coffee. Taste is thick, sweet; toffee, caramel & coffee. Finish is clean, not what I expecte from a "lager".
Mostly disappointing, pours a cloudy, particle laden yellow with a thin, white head that fades quick. Aroma is citrus and the taste is a sweet sour citrus with a bitter aftertaste.

Dark brown, almost black body with a medium creamy head. Aroma is sweet licorice and roast toffee. The taste is sweet chocolate, carmel with a bit of an alcoholic aftertaste. Finish is slightly bitter, but mostly clean.

Not impressive at all. Should have gotten my first clue in the pour, virtually no carbonation, looks like a flat cola. Aroma is fruity, banana, citrus, etc. Taste is overwhelmingly spices, nutmeg, ginger with hints of citrus. Finish is slightly bitter. This would have been better off a baked good than a beer, not recommended.

Nothing exceptional, pours a clean yellow with a thick white head and nice lacing. Aroma is doughy with hints of corn. Taste is crisp, slightly bitter but not bad. Finish is again crisp with little aftertaste.

Nice dark body with a creamy head and good lacing. Nutty aroma with hints of caramel. Taste is subtle coffee, hops and sweetness. Pleasant finish, enjoyable.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Boulevard Tasting Room Series Black Pale Ale

review_blob: Cloudy orange with a thick white head. Aroma is pine, hops and slight dough. Taste is slightly sweet for an IPA and not quite as bitter. Goes down fairly easy with a slight bitter finish.
beer_name: Boulevard Tasting Room Series Belgian-Style IPA

review_blob:
Found this at an Omaha HyVee. Definitely on the marzen side of lagers. Amber body with hardly any head. Faint aroma. Taste is sweet, slight hops with a little after taste.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

A local favorite I've had several times, yet have not gotten around to rating until now. Thick beige head with a cloudy amber body. Aroma is hops with pine. Obviously hoppy favor with slight citrus and a mildly bitter finish.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Very similar to an IPA in aroma, yet with a milder taste. Not much of an IPA fan I can appreciate the slight sweetness and less bitter finish. Has a cloudy body with a nice gold color and a medium white head with nice lacing. Not bad.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Nice, clean amber body with white head. Aroma is faint, with subtle sweetness. Taste is strong, sweet grains and roast caramel, a little too front loaded. Finish is mostly clean with some bitterness. Not what I was expecting and a bit disappointed.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

The first cider I've rated. Pours a nice pale yellow, aroma is, well... apples. Taste is sweet and tart with a slightly bitter aftertaste. Not bad.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Part of the Fall Seasonal Sampler. Not a big IPA fan, but this wasn't bad. Nice deep amber body, with a thick white head and nice lacing. Aroma is subtle sweetness, roasted caramel. Taste is hoppy yet smooth, hints of caramel and coffee. Finishes remarkably clean without the bitterness I find in most IPAs.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Nice deep amber body, thick white head. Smells of spice and hops, taste is sweet, but not overpowering, carmel, spice and some fruitiness. Finish has a little bitter bite, that fades quick.
A slightly sweet mrzen with a medium yellow body and a nice white head and impressive lacing. Slightly earthy smell with hints of spice. Taste is crisp, hoppy with a slightly bitter aftertaste.

Standard medium, yellow body with a thin white head. Aroma is faint hops, citrus and pine. Taste is lightly bitter, yet crisp. Hops with some fruit, yet not overly sweet at all. Finishes clean. not bad.

Another odd-ball from Aldi, although I think I like this one better than the Bacher I tried from there last time. Has a faint hops aroma with a pale to medium body and thin white head.Taste is grains, slight hay. Finishes crisp and clean, for the price its definitely recommendable.

Picked this up at my local Aldis. Suprisingly most of their knock-off beers have been pretty good, so I thought Id give it a try. Pours a pale yellow with a thin white head and decent lacing. Aroma is faint hops and the taste is thin, slightly astringent and watery. Finishes clean. Although its not the most flavorful, its fairly easy to drink.
Orangish-yellow body & thin white head that disappears quickly. Little or no aroma and the taste is sweet, slightly metallic. Slight aftertaste, no bad but nothing exceptional.
Nice yellow body with a slight haze and a lasting, thick white head. The aroma is sweet, slightly moldy.Taste is smooth with a tiny bite, but in a good way, finish is crisp and clean.

Pours a classic deep yellow with a medium white head. Nice lacing and good carbonation. Aroma is faint and mildly sweet. Taste is crisp and goes down easy, finishes clean.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

On tap at Grinders downtown KC, pours a nice copper-orange with a thick white head that lasts. Aroma is hops, some pine. Taste is a more subtle hops, slightly mild for an IPA. Finish is clean, recommended.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: A deep dark body with a creamy head. Aroma is faint, almost nonexistent. Slight coffee and sweetness. Taste is also subtle coffee and and caramel, not much vanilla . Finish is clean, was expecting more.
A medium orange body with virtually no head. Aroma is hoppy, almost, piney, taste is pretty much the same. Finishes dry with a lingering bitter bite.

Nice red body with a creamy head. Nice carbonation and lacing. The aroma is a sweet, roasted caramel and coffee. Taste is sweet, with slight hops and toffee. Finish is clean, easy to drink and recommended.

6-Pack from Trader Joess. Non distinct aroma and appearance. Classic medium body with a nice white head. Taste is hops with hints of corn, pine and a slightly seer caramel finish. Drinks easy, not bad especially given the price.
I like pumpkin pie, I love beer so why not? Pours a cloudy orange with a medium white head. Aroma is cinnamon & nutmeg and the taste is the same. Pleasantly sweet, yet not overwhelming. Enjoyable.

Without question, not remarkable, but
 easy to drink. Pours a medium yellow with a thin white that fades quick. Aroma is slight hops as is the taste. Like I said this is non-impressionable, yet enjoyable.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

An enjoyable IPA that pours a cloudy amber with a thin whitehead that fades quick. Aroma is hops and pine. Taste is also hoppy with citrus notes. A typical IPA with a clean finish.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Hazy yellow body with a soapy white head. Aroma is pine with citrus notes. Taste is crisp hops with slight sweetness and a bitter finish. Slight dry aftertaste. Fairly typical IPA, drinkable enough.

12 oz. bottle from the local Trader Joe's. Deep amber body with a medium tan head that fades quick and decent lacing. Smells of bread, slight hops and spice. Taste is again bread with a subtle sweetness and some ginger. Sight aftertaste.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Almost cola-like in appearance, clear-brown body with a medium tan head. Decent lacing. Smell is sweet, nutty with hints of coffee. Taste is roast hops, coffee & slight chocolate. Finishes fairly clean.

Although, not distinguishable in appearance, this is a refreshing brew. Crisp taste with a clean finish. Not bad.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
Light yellow body with a thin white head, Aroma is grass, hay & mold. Taste is slightly sweet, hints of bread and citrus. Finishes clean.

16 oz. can from Trader Joes here in Kansas City. Classic medium yellow body with a thick white head that sticks around.Aroma is slightly musty with yeast and moldy hay.Taste is grass, rice and alcohol, slightly sweet, yet pretty smooth. Slight after taste, but easy to drink.

Slightly cloudy yellow body with a medium white head. Aroma is orange & nutmeg. Taste is a fresh citrus with definite spice overtones. Finishes fairly clean. Not a huge wheat ale fan, but this I enjoyed.

In a word: thin. Thin pale body, with a almost non-exisent head. Thin aroma, slight corn and grain, but you really need to put your nose to it. Thin taste, astringent and almost soapy. Finish is quick and crisp. Not bed, just not much there.

My first South American brew. The body is totally opaque with a purplish cream head that fades quick. Aroma is very light and almost soapy. Taste is a rich, coffee, toffee blend that finishes relatively clean. Heavy flavor, yet smooth.
Nice, deep amber body with a thin white head. Aroma is clean, slightly floral, slightly sweet. Taste is sweet caramel, some fruit with a slight bitter alcohol finish.
beer_name: Black Sheep Monty Pythons Holy Grail (Bottle)

review_blob:
Part of a World Beers sampler from World Market. Faint aroma is dough, grass and stale hay. The body is pale yellow with a medium head and decent lacing. Taste is light, slight hops and straw. Crisp & medicinal aftertaste.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Not a big pale ale fan, but I liked this. A cloudy yellow body with an aroma of hops & spice. Taste is dry, crisp & hoppy. Slightly bitter, yet clean finish.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
